Add intensity metrics — mark_intensity
text: function adds several columns dataset contains accelerometer counts data. columns concern respectively sedentary time (SED), light physical activity time (LPA), moderate physical activity time (MPA), vigorous physical activity time (VPA), metabolic equivalent task (METs), kilocalories (kcal), MET-hours time spent moderate--vigorous physical activity, step-based metrics (maximum step accumulation peak step accumulation metrics). SED, LPA, MPA, VPA columns, function provides, epoch, numeric value 1 value configured counts variable corresponds criteria considered category (e.g., <150 counts/min sedentary behavior); , 0 provided. METs computed using compute_mets function. METs computed weight, sex, accelerometer counts, published equation one following scientific articles: Sasaki et al. (2011; doi:10.1016/j.jsams.2011.04.003); Santos-Lozano et al. (2013; 10.1055/s-0033-1337945); Freedson et al. (1998; doi: 10.1097/00005768-199805000-00021). Kilocalories computed multiplying METs basal metabolic rate (BMR) expressed kcal/min non-SED epochs (SED epochs, BMR expressed kcal/min directly used). BMR computed using compute_bmr function uses sex, age, weight inputs, one equations retrieved paper Henry et al. (2005; doi: 10.1079/PHN2005801). MET-hours obtained multiplying METs time related epoch (1/60e hour), MET value  >=3.

title: Prepare accelerometer data — prepare_dataset
text: function performs following actions: reads .agd file, collapses accelerometer data based configured epoch length (now, 60 s can used), creates vector magnitude variable, creates date time columns, finally organizes columns given order. .agd file must contain least following columns: axis1 axis2 axis3 steps inclinestanding inclinesitting inclinelying

TEE obtained summing kilocalories measured wear time epochs kilocalories likely expended nonwear time epochs (, kilocalories associated BMR, assumed device mainly worn sleeping periods , periods energy expenditure near BMR), multiplying sum 10/9 take account thermic effect food. course, calculations may conduct underestimate TEE PAL device removed prolonged periods physical activity. Moreover, even device correctly worn, estimate PAL approximate since BMR kilocalories related wear time estimated using methods may accurate individual level.
